Nonlinear systems abound. The mathematician
Stanislaw Ulam is reputed to have once said that
referring to nonlinear systems as natural is like 
referring to the bulk of the animal kingdom as "non-
elephant animals."

The study of nonlinear systems is like the study of non-elephant biology.

Quantity is no substitute for quality, but it's the only one I've got.

